This module includes copies of, and data derived from, the official XRechnung
3.0.2 artifacts published by KoSIT (Koordinierungsstelle für IT-Standards) on
behalf of xeinkauf.de, namely:

  - the XRechnung semantic model (SeMoX), used to derive the German rule/field
    texts and the BT/BG terms each rule constrains;
  - the EN16931 validation artifacts and the XRechnung validation Schematron,
    used to derive the English rule texts, rule identifiers and severities;
  - the XRechnung visualization localization files, used to derive German and
    English business-term labels;
  - the XRechnung test suite, a curated subset of whose invoice instances is
    bundled under testdata/ for round-trip and validation tests.

Those artifacts are licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0.
See https://xeinkauf.de/xrechnung/ and https://github.com/itplr-kosit.

Verbatim copies of the specific source artifacts used for code generation are
bundled under internal/gen/resources/ (see that directory's README for the file
list and provenance); data derived from them is compiled into the
internal/catalog package; and a subset of the test suite instances is bundled
under testdata/. This NOTICE provides the attribution that the Apache-2.0
license requires for all of these, and must be retained in redistributions.
